    "content": "This guide walks you through the app from start to finish. Use the sidebar or the links below to jump to a section. Quick links - [Getting Started](/guide/getting-started) — Install and first run - [UI Overview](/guide/ui-overview) — Main interface and toolbar - [Add Files & Jobs](/guide/add-files-jobs) — Import videos (Files or Folder) - [Targets & Visibility](/guide/exports) — YT / IG / TT targets, visibility per video - [Schedule per platform](/guide/scheduler) — Schedule for YouTube, Instagram, TikTok - [Plan (bulk)](/guide/scheduler) — Bulk scheduling with presets - [Publish](/guide/youtube-connect-upload) — Workflow and Auto Upload - [Manual Assist](/guide/manual-assist) — How IG/TikTok assist works - [Troubleshooting](/guide/troubleshooting) — Common issues and fixes --- Quick start (recommended) **Standard workflow** 1. Keep **Auto Plan (⏰)** ON (default). 2. Set your preferred platform in **Plan** dialog \"Apply to\" (this becomes the default for future imports). 3. Click **Add (Files or Folder)** and import videos (Files or Folder). - Targets are automatically enabled based on your last Plan \"Apply to\" setting - Videos are automatically scheduled 4. Check or adjust **Targets (YT / IG / TT)** and **Visibility** if needed. 5. On each platform column, click **Schedule** if you want a different time. 6. Enable **Auto Upload (🚀)** only when you are ready. **Manual control workflow** 1. Set **Auto Plan (⏰)** OFF. 2. Import videos (they will not be auto-scheduled, all targets default to OFF). 3. Enable the target you want (e.g. YT only) and click **Schedule** in that platform column. 4. Enable **Auto Upload (🚀)** only when you want automatic execution. \"Planning\" (Auto Plan / Plan dialog) is different from \"execution\" (Auto Upload). You can have a schedule set without Auto Upload running. --- How Auto Plan works When **Auto Plan** is ON and you import videos: - Targets are automatically enabled based on the last **Plan** dialog \"Apply to\" setting: - If last Plan was set to **YouTube**, only YouTube target is enabled - If last Plan was set to **Instagram**, only Instagram target is enabled - If last Plan was set to **TikTok**, only TikTok target is enabled - If last Plan was set to **All**, YouTube target is enabled by default (safe default) - The app calculates dates and times from your plan defaults (start date, time slots, time zone). - It creates scheduled jobs (one per platform per row) for each enabled target. When **Auto Plan** is OFF: - Imported videos are not scheduled. - All targets default to OFF. - You must manually enable targets and use Schedule or Plan to assign times. --- How Targets and Visibility work - **Targets** — Targets are stored per row and control which platforms will be scheduled when you use Schedule or Plan. Targets are enabled automatically when you schedule a platform (by clicking Schedule in the YouTube/Instagram/TikTok column), or when you use the Plan dialog \"Apply to\" setting. There is no separate UI to directly toggle targets — they are managed implicitly through scheduling actions. - **Visibility** — Set Private / Unlisted / Public (YouTube). Stored per row and displayed in the Visibility column. Targets determine which platforms get scheduled jobs when you use Schedule or Plan. When you schedule a platform for a video (by clicking Schedule in the YouTube/Instagram/TikTok column), that platform's target is automatically enabled. You can also enable targets in bulk using the Plan dialog \"Apply to\" setting. --- How Schedule works (per platform) For each platform (YouTube, Instagram, TikTok): 1. Ensure the target for that platform is ON. 2. In the **Jobs table**, click the **cell** for that platform (YouTube, Instagram, or TikTok) to open the **Schedule for [platform]** dialog. 3. Choose **Schedule for later** and set **Date & time**, or **Upload now** / **Open now** / **Assist now** for immediate action. 4. Click **Schedule** (or **Upload now** / **Open now** / **Assist now**) — a scheduled job is created for that platform and appears in the queue. You can have different times for YouTube, Instagram, and TikTok for the same video. --- How Plan works (bulk scheduling) Use **Plan** when you want to apply the same time pattern to multiple selected rows: 1. Select rows (checkboxes in the Jobs table). 2. Click **Plan** in the command bar. 3. Set **Targets** (All / YouTube / Instagram / TikTok), **start date**, **time zone**, and **times** (presets: 3/day, 4/day, Hourly, or custom). 4. Click **Apply to N items** (N = number of selected rows). **How \"Apply to\" works:** - **All** — Enables all 3 targets (YouTube, Instagram, TikTok) and creates scheduled jobs for all platforms - **YouTube / Instagram / TikTok** — Enables only that platform's target and creates scheduled jobs only for that platform - The selected \"Apply to\" setting is saved and used as the default for future imports when Auto Plan is ON Plan applies only to **unscheduled** platform slots in the selection; rows that already have a time for a platform keep it. --- How Auto Upload works Auto Upload runs in the background when enabled. It polls for due scheduled jobs in the queue and: - **YouTube** — Uploads automatically. - **Instagram / TikTok** — Manual Assist: copies caption+hashtags to clipboard, opens browser and Explorer (unless Silent Mode is ON). **Silent Mode ON** — Only shows the assist overlay; no automatic browser/Explorer opening. Click the overlay to trigger assist. **Silent Mode OFF** — Opens browser and Explorer automatically when a scheduled job is due (once per scheduled job, not on every poll). The app must be running (in system tray) for Auto Upload to work. --- Next steps Browse the full guide in the sidebar. Start with [Getting Started](/guide/getting-started) if you are new."
